---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const effectiveDate = "April 21, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy · Rangeway"
  description="What personal information Rangeway collects, how we use it, and your rights regarding that information."
>
  <section class="section legal">
    <div class="container-narrow legal__body reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal__effective"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> {effectiveDate}</p>

      <p>
        Rangeway Energy, Inc. ("Rangeway," "we," "us," or "our") operates the website at
        rangeway.co and related subdomains (collectively, the "Site"). This Privacy Policy
        explains what personal information we collect, how we use it, and your rights
        regarding that information.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        We collect only the information you provide directly or that is generated through
        ordinary website analytics.
      </p>

      <p><strong>Information you provide:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Contact form submissions:</strong> When you submit the contact form, we
          collect your name, email address, interest category, and message.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Field Notes newsletter subscriptions:</strong> When you subscribe to our
          newsletter, we collect your email address. Field Notes is operated through
          Buttondown, a third-party newsletter platform.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p><strong>Information collected automatically:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics:</strong> We use Tinylytics, a privacy-focused analytics service,
          to understand how visitors use the Site. Tinylytics collects aggregated,
          non-identifying information such as page views, referring URLs, browser type, and
          coarse geographic region (for example, country or state). Tinylytics does not use
          cookies or fingerprinting and does not track individual users across sites.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p><strong>Information we do not collect:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>We do not use cookies.</li>
        <li>We do not use advertising or retargeting trackers.</li>
        <li>
          We do not collect financial information, account credentials, or sensitive personal
          information through the Site.
        </li>
        <li>We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use the information you provide for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>To respond to your inquiries submitted through the contact form</li>
        <li>
          To route your inquiry to the appropriate internal team (press, investor relations,
          partnerships, careers, or general)
        </li>
        <li>To send you Field Notes newsletter emails if you subscribed</li>
        <li>To maintain ordinary business records</li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
        <li>
          To improve the Site and understand how visitors use it (using aggregated analytics
          only)
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Third-Party Service Providers</h2>
      <p>We use the following third-party services to operate the Site:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>GitHub Pages:</strong> Hosts the Site.</li>
        <li>
          <strong>Formsubmit.co:</strong> Processes contact form submissions and routes them
          to our internal email inbox.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Buttondown:</strong> Operates our Field Notes newsletter. Subscriber email
          addresses are stored by Buttondown under their privacy practices, available at
          <a href="https://buttondown.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">buttondown.com/privacy</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Tinylytics:</strong> Provides aggregated website analytics. Tinylytics'
          privacy practices are available at
          <a href="https://tinylytics.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tinylytics.app</a>.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Each of these providers processes data according to their own privacy policies. We
        encourage you to review them.
      </p>

      <h2>4. How We Share Your Information</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information. We do not share your
        personal information with third parties for their marketing purposes.
      </p>
      <p>We share information only in these limited circumstances:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          With the third-party service providers listed above, as necessary to operate the
          Site
        </li>
        <li>
          When required by law, such as in response to a subpoena, court order, or government
          request
        </li>
        <li>To protect our legal rights, prevent fraud, or address security concerns</li>
        <li>
          In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or substantially all of
          our assets, in which case we will notify affected users
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain contact form submissions and newsletter subscriber information for as long
        as necessary to respond to your inquiry, provide ongoing communications, and maintain
        business records. You may request deletion of your information at any time by
        contacting us (see Section 9).
      </p>

      <h2>6. Your Rights if You Live in California</h2>
      <p>
        If you are a California resident, the California Consumer Privacy Act ("CCPA") gives
        you the following rights:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to know:</strong> You may request information about the personal
          information we have collected about you, including the categories of information,
          the sources of the information, the purposes for collecting it, and the third
          parties with whom we share it.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to delete:</strong> You may request that we delete personal
          information we have collected from you, subject to certain exceptions.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to correct:</strong> You may request that we correct inaccurate
          personal information we maintain about you.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to opt out of sale or sharing:</strong> We do not sell or share
          personal information as those terms are defined under the CCPA. There is nothing to
          opt out of.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to non-discrimination:</strong> We will not discriminate against you
          for exercising your CCPA rights.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:legal@rangeway.co">legal@rangeway.co</a>. We may need to verify
        your identity before processing your request.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Your Rights if You Live in the European Economic Area or United Kingdom</h2>
      <p>
        If you are located in the European Economic Area, the United Kingdom, or another
        jurisdiction covered by the General Data Protection Regulation ("GDPR") or UK GDPR,
        you have the following rights regarding your personal information:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Right of access to your personal information</li>
        <li>Right to rectification of inaccurate information</li>
        <li>Right to erasure ("right to be forgotten")</li>
        <li>Right to restrict processing</li>
        <li>Right to data portability</li>
        <li>Right to object to processing</li>
        <li>Right to withdraw consent where processing is based on consent</li>
        <li>Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The legal bases on which we process personal information under GDPR include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Consent</strong> for newsletter subscriptions (you may withdraw consent at
          any time by unsubscribing)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Legitimate interests</strong> for responding to contact form submissions and
          operating the Site
        </li>
        <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> where required by law</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:legal@rangeway.co">legal@rangeway.co</a>. We will respond within
        the timeframes required by applicable law.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Security</h2>
      <p>
        We take reasonable administrative, technical, and physical measures to protect the
        information we collect. However, no method of transmission or storage is completely
        secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For questions about this Privacy Policy or to exercise your privacy rights, contact us
        at:
      </p>
      <address class="legal__address">
        Rangeway Energy, Inc.<br />
        2661 Market Street, STE 85787<br />
        San Francisco, CA 94114<br />
        <a href="mailto:legal@rangeway.co">legal@rangeway.co</a>
      </address>

      <h2>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we
        will update the Effective Date at the top of this page and, where appropriate, notify
        users through the Site. Your continued use of the Site after changes become effective
        constitutes your acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal__body {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .legal__body h1 {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .legal__body h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .legal__body p,
  .legal__body ul {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-5);
    max-width: 72ch;
  }

  .legal__body ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .legal__body ul li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .legal__body a {
    color: var(--color-warm-deep);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .legal__body a:hover {
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  .legal__effective {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-7);
  }

  .legal__address {
    font-style: normal;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
</style>
